[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Skips the fishing mini-game. Cast your line and the mod handles the rest — no timing the click, no tracking the bobber.[/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][b]Instant hook[/b] — fish bite the moment the line is cast. The vanilla reel-in mini-game is bypassed entirely.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Auto-loot[/b] — the catch lands straight in your inventory. You don't need to walk over to pick it up.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Loot table untouched[/b] — you catch exactly what vanilla would have given you (same fish types, same rarity distribution). This is a convenience mod, not a loot-booster.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]No unlocks[/b] — requires the vanilla fishing rod. Once you've got a rod, the mod is active.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/70]Give Me Moar[/url] — includes a Miscellaneous category multiplier for fish/water-related drops if you want bigger catches.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/42]Exhaust-less[/url] — if fishing often, halve its energy cost or go unlimited.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/53]Longer Days[/url] — longer day cycle means more productive fishing sessions between sleeps.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/62]Where's Ma' Storage[/url] — shared inventory so caught fish flow into every kitchen and bench that uses them.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper&#92;BepInEx[/code][/size]

